SMALLOS(7)

NAME
    smallos - overview of the SmallOS user environment

DESCRIPTION
    SmallOS boots a protected-mode kernel, mounts an ext2 filesystem, and
    launches the user shell. Most user programs are installed as ELF files
    under /bin, /usr/bin, /usr/sbin, or /usr/libexec/tests.

    Commands can usually be run by basename from the shell. The shell searches
    common program directories and can add the .elf suffix automatically.

FILESYSTEM
    The root filesystem is ext2. Common paths include:

    /bin
        Core user commands.

    /usr/bin
        Demo and development commands.

    /usr/sbin
        Service-style commands.

    /usr/libexec/tests
        Diagnostic and self-test programs.

    /usr/share/man
        Plain text manual pages.

    /var/log
        Service and boot logs.

NETWORKING
    The image includes IPv4 configuration tools, simple ICMP and ARP probes,
    an FTP server, and an HTTP server. In QEMU user networking, host forwards
    are needed for inbound services.

MANUALS
    SmallOS manual pages are plain text files. Use man(1) to view them.

SEE ALSO
    shell(1), man(1), ip(1), ftpd(8), cserve(8)
